; Regression test for issue #2946: regex backslash escaping.
;
; In ledger regex literals (/pattern/), backslash handling must satisfy:
;   \/ → /  (escaped delimiter, backslash stripped)
;   \\ → \  (escaped backslash, collapsed for backward compatibility)
;   \X → \X (all other escapes pass through to the regex engine)
;
; PR #2902 (fix #1781) changed from C-style escape stripping to passthrough,
; which broke users who wrote \\* to match literal stars.  Adding \\→\
; collapsing restores backward compatibility while keeping the #1781 fix.

tag rating
    assert value =~ /^\\*{0,5}$/

2018/12/31 * Test
    Expenses:Foo     $100           ; rating: ***
    Assets:Checking

test bal
               $-100  Assets:Checking
                $100  Expenses:Foo
--------------------
                   0
end test
